		<item>
		<title>How to Make the Metronome Swing (L#163)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/rhythm/make-the-metronome-swing-bass-lesson.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/rhythm/make-the-metronome-swing-bass-lesson.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2015 12:47:58 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[scott]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Bass Lines & Grooves]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Rhythm]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Walking Bass Lines]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=10615</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>When I tell people you can make a metronome actually ‘swing’ I get some funny looks to say the least… But, you certainly can make it swing! A metronome can be an invaluable tool for bass players that are seeking...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/rhythm/make-the-metronome-swing-bass-lesson.html">How to Make the Metronome Swing (L#163)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>When I tell people you can make a metronome actually ‘swing’ I get some funny looks to say the least…</p>
<p>But, you certainly can make it <em>swing</em>!</p>
<p>A metronome can be an invaluable tool for bass players that are seeking to develop their groove and time feel. The key, is to find ways of using the metronome in a <em>musical way</em> that re-enforces your internal subdivision feel and in turn develops your overall groove.</p>
<p>In the past few lessons we’ve focused on getting your <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/rythm/shuffle-bass-lesson.html" target="_blank">shuffle feel</a> together and strengthening your <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/rythm/bass-groove-lesson.html" target="_blank">eighth note grooves</a>. In this lesson you’re going to learn how to make the metronome swing.</p>
<p>We’re going to start off slowly, so if you’re just starting out playing swing - this lesson will be great for you.</p>
<p>If you’re a more advanced player, don’t worry - I’ve included some exercises in this lesson that are going to make you <em>sweat</em>! ;)</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
</p>
